1
00:00:01,859 --> 00:00:04,717
January 13, 1979

2
00:00:09,374 --> 00:00:11,077
Shake it, baby.

3
00:00:11,319 --> 00:00:13,281
I just finished reading 
The Feminine Mystique,

4
00:00:13,281 --> 00:00:15,916
and I don't get it,  Alison. I mean,

5
00:00:15,916 --> 00:00:17,483
I'm not some kind of man-hater.

6
00:00:17,483 --> 00:00:19,913
Cause there's so much to love.

7
00:00:23,183 --> 00:00:28,412
I mean, I'm proud, being a housewife,
a mother. I don't hate my life.

8
00:00:28,412 --> 00:00:31,389
Well, hating your life isn't 
Betty's point. / Then what is?

9
00:00:31,389 --> 00:00:35,342
Loving it.
Do you love your life, Libby?

10
00:00:35,823 --> 00:00:38,115
Last chance, macho men.

11
00:00:38,115 --> 00:00:41,605
If your keys aren't in the bowl, I can't pick'em!

12
00:00:41,605 --> 00:00:43,334
Whoo! You heard my wife!

13
00:00:43,334 --> 00:00:46,640
Time to get real free and real naked!

14
00:00:47,491 --> 00:00:50,185
- Now that's women's lib for you.
- What's going on?

15
00:00:50,185 --> 00:00:52,228
Carl didn't tell you?

16
00:00:53,279 --> 00:00:57,364
It's a key party.
Everyone's doing it.

17
00:00:57,757 --> 00:01:00,002
Not everyone.

18
00:01:03,289 --> 00:01:05,436
Carl, let's go.

19
00:01:05,436 --> 00:01:08,764
- What? We just got here.
- I want to go home.

20
00:01:08,764 --> 00:01:10,799
Loosen up, Lib.
Get yourself a drink.

21
00:01:10,799 --> 00:01:13,269
You knew about this, didn't you?

22
00:01:14,591 --> 00:01:16,968
I promised Joe I'd play.

23
00:01:16,968 --> 00:01:18,916
It's something he heard about 
when he was in California.

24
00:01:18,916 --> 00:01:21,053
We live in Pennsylvania.

25
00:01:21,389 --> 00:01:22,775
It's just a game, Lib.

26
00:01:22,775 --> 00:01:27,444
When Joe got home, he left his wife
for a 23-year-old stewardess.

27
00:01:28,897 --> 00:01:31,615
It's not just a game.

28
00:01:32,903 --> 00:01:35,362
Take a cab, then. I'm staying.

29
00:01:35,362 --> 00:01:37,245
God knows it's been a frigid winter.

30
00:01:37,245 --> 00:01:40,675
Let's go, foxy ladies.
You pick his keychain,

31
00:01:40,675 --> 00:01:44,035
and he sticks his keys in your ignition.

32
00:01:46,127 --> 00:01:48,648
Who's gonna kick things off?

33
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:54,209
I will.

34
00:01:55,347 --> 00:01:57,096
Libby?

35
00:01:57,556 --> 00:01:59,638
I said, I will.

36
00:02:13,652 --> 00:02:16,821
Who's the lucky macho man?

37
00:02:29,340 --> 00:02:30,983
Mom?

38
00:02:32,390 --> 00:02:34,678
- Mom!
- I hate this part.

39
00:02:34,678 --> 00:02:39,419
Mom! Mommy!
Mom! Oh!

40
00:02:39,419 --> 00:02:40,809
Young lady, you're gonna 
have to step back.

41
00:02:40,809 --> 00:02:43,253
Oh, my God!

42
00:02:44,309 --> 00:02:46,271
That's my mom!

43
00:02:48,779 --> 00:02:51,064
Breathe.
Breathe.

44
00:02:51,064 --> 00:02:53,482
Just breathe.
Just breathe.

45
00:02:53,482 --> 00:02:55,317
You're going to be all right.

46
00:02:59,865 --> 00:03:02,613
We'll find the person who did this.

47
00:03:03,148 --> 00:03:05,075
You will?

48
00:03:05,572 --> 00:03:07,305
Yeah.

49
00:03:08,262 --> 00:03:09,988
I promise.

50
00:03:45,623 --> 00:03:47,369
Got here fast as we could, Will.

51
00:03:47,369 --> 00:03:49,595
Missing my beauty sleep.
Better be good.

52
00:03:49,595 --> 00:03:54,130
Kids camping out, having some sort
of Blair Witch scarefest.

53
00:03:54,130 --> 00:03:55,415
Making a movie?

54
00:03:55,415 --> 00:03:56,870
Looking for a ghost.

55
00:03:56,870 --> 00:03:58,528
As in Casper the Friendly?

56
00:03:58,528 --> 00:04:00,276
Libby Bradley.

57
00:04:00,276 --> 00:04:02,302
Found stabbed in tse woods, 1979.

58
00:04:02,302 --> 00:04:04,994
Kids been calling the place
haunted ever since.

59
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:06,262
What'd they find?

60
00:04:06,262 --> 00:04:09,782
Ski jacket stuffed in a tree trunk.
Doer must've dumped it.

61
00:04:09,782 --> 00:04:11,926
Amount of blood looks like a stabbing.

62
00:04:11,926 --> 00:04:14,058
From 27 years ago.

63
00:04:14,058 --> 00:04:16,226
Half mile from where we found her.

64
00:04:16,226 --> 00:04:18,939
A few hundred yards
beyond our search area.

65
00:04:18,939 --> 00:04:20,449
Called her daughter to ID it.

66
00:04:20,449 --> 00:04:23,341
You called a family member 
at 2:00 a.m. over a jacket?

67
00:04:23,341 --> 00:04:26,668
She's been calling me for 27 years.

68
00:04:26,668 --> 00:04:29,009
You worked the job back in '79?

69
00:04:29,009 --> 00:04:31,360
And made a promise I couldn't keep.

70
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:33,298
Rookie mistake.

71
00:04:33,868 --> 00:04:35,450
Will?

72
00:04:39,262 --> 00:04:40,851
Helen.

73
00:04:40,851 --> 00:04:43,013
Detectives Rush, Vera.

74
00:04:44,820 --> 00:04:46,736
You found something?

75
00:04:46,736 --> 00:04:51,038
Ski jacket.
Thinking it might be your mom's.

76
00:04:52,814 --> 00:04:54,569
Oh, my God.

77
00:04:54,972 --> 00:04:56,889
You recognize it?

78
00:04:57,311 --> 00:05:01,615
She used to call it her bumblebee jacket
because of the black stripe.

79
00:05:03,771 --> 00:05:07,330
Found this in the pocket.
Car keys.

80
00:05:07,330 --> 00:05:10,219
- That doesn't make sense.
- What doesn't?

81
00:05:10,219 --> 00:05:13,164
- Those car keys couldn't be hers.
- Why not?

82
00:05:13,164 --> 00:05:16,328
Because my mother didn't know 
how to drive.

